  "text": "BCL-6-mediated non-transcriptional regulation of the dark zone phenotype. BCL-6 is known to recruit several co-repressors. Transcriptional repression can be achieved through various mechanisms. In one such mechanism, it was found that the enhancers of certain BCL-6 target genes remain poised for activation or repression [CITATION_1] . This poised configuration is achieved by the selective recruitment of histone deacetylase 3 (HDAC3)-containing SMRT (silencing mediator for retinoic acid receptor and thyroid hormone receptor; also known as NCOR2) co-repressor complexes by BCL-6 to certain enhancers to achieve repression via H3K27 deacetylation. This effect is counterbalanced by p300 complexes that enable H3K27 acetylation and enhancer activation. Competition between these two events thereby allows reversible 'toggling' of the expression of key GC genes and, similarly to EZH2, allows dynamic regulation of BCL-6 target genes as the GC reaction proceeds and cells transition into diverse phenotypic fates.",
  "correct_citation": {
